{{Use British English|date=February 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date=February 2015}} {{Spanish name|'''Grullón'''|'''Espaillat'''}} '''Alejandro Enrique Grullón Espaillat''' ([[Santiago de los Caballeros]], 1929) is a businessman from the [[Dominican Republic]].
== Biography == Grullón Espaillat was born to Manuel Alejandro Grullón Rodríguez-Objío (1895–1985) and Amantina Rafaela Espaillat González (1903–2006). He married Ana Dínorah Viñas Messina (1952–2001) and later after he divorced, then he married Melba Segura Castillo (?–).
He founded ''{{Interlanguage link multi|Banco Popular Dominicano|es}}'' in January 1964, today the largest private bank in the Dominican Republic. He was the chairman of the Board of Directors of ''Grupo Popular'' until April 2014, when he leave his post to his son [[Manuel Alejandro Grullón]] (1953–).<ref name=eldia>{{cite news|title=Don Alejandro Grullón le pasa la antorcha a su hijo Manuel en el Banco Popular|url=http://eldia.com.do/don-alejandro-grullon-le-pasa-la-antorcha-a-su-hijo-manuel-en-el-banco-popular/|accessdate=2 February 2015|agency=El Día|date=27 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150202104931/http://eldia.com.do/don-alejandro-grullon-le-pasa-la-antorcha-a-su-hijo-manuel-en-el-banco-popular/|archivedate=2 February 2015|location=Santo Domingo|language=Spanish}}</ref> He is also co-founder of the [[NGO]] ''Fundación Sur Futuro''.
