{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}} '''Duncan Douglas Foulds Rae OBE''' (14 June 1931 &ndash; 23 June 2018), commonly known as '''Douglas Rae''', was a [[Scotland|Scottish]] businessman. He was chairman of the Golden Casket confectionery corporation<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/business-news/2008/07/18/golden-casket-enjoying-sweet-time-after-profits-boost-86908-20653226/|title=Golden Casket enjoying sweet time after profits boost|publisher=[[Daily Record (Scotland)|Daily Record]]|date=18 July 2008}}</ref> (best known for Buchanan's Toffees and Millions), as well as chairman of [[Greenock Morton F.C.|Greenock Morton]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/football/sfl/2009/11/16/referees-need-tech-support-to-avoid-more-blunders-says-morton-chairman-douglas-rae-86908-21825505/|title=Referees need tech support to avoid more blunders, says Morton chairman Douglas Rae|publisher=[[Daily Record (Scotland)|Daily Record]]|date=16 November 2009}}</ref> He was appointed OBE in the [[2016 Birthday Honours]].
In April 2018, Rae stood down as chairman of Morton and handed the reins to his son Crawford, who also runs Golden Casket.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://gmfc.net/2018/04/28/from-the-office-of-the-chairman/|title=From the office of the chairman|publisher=Greenock Morton F.C.|date=28 April 2018|accessdate=30 April 2018|first=Douglas|last=Rae OBE}}</ref>
He died on 23 June 2018 at the age of 87.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.greenocktelegraph.co.uk/news/16310622.former-morton-chairman-douglas-rae-has-died/|title=Former Morton chairman Douglas Rae has died|publisher=Greenock Telegraph|first=Russell|last=Steele|date=24 June 2018|accessdate=25 June 2018}}</ref>
