'''Notion''' is a [[note-taking]] application with markdown support that also integrates tasks, wikis, and databases. The aim is to be an all-in-one workspace for note-taking, project management and task management. <ref>{{cite web |url = https://androidcommunity.com/notion-goes-where-evernote-dares-not-what-you-need-to-know-20180608/ |title = Notion goes where Evernote dares not: what you need to know |date = 8 June 2018 |work = [[Android Community]]}}</ref> In addition to cross-platform apps, it can be accessed via most [[web browser]]s and it has [[markdown]] syntax support.<ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-only-app-you-need-for-work-life-productivity-1521640800 |title = The Only App You Need for Work-Life Productivity  |date = 21 March 2018 |work = [[The Wall Street Journal]]}}</ref>

==History==

Notion Labs Inc is a startup based in San Francisco, born in 2016. Some of the main investors are [[Josh Kopelman]], an American entrepreneur and venture capitalist, and [[Ram Shriram]], a founding board member and one of the first investors in Google. 

In June, 2018, an official app for Android was released.<ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.theverge.com/2018/6/7/17434754/notion-android-app-notes-productivity-review |title = Notion brings its powerful note-taking app to Android |date = 7 June 2018 |work = [[The Verge]]}}</ref>

